# === Narrative ===

THIS SUBJECT IDENTIFIES_AS a scientist working out whether mind is mechanizable.
  @LAYER narrative  @AUTHOR ai  @CONFIDENCE 0.80
  @SOURCES [text/papers/computing-machinery-1950.md,
            text/letters/morcom-1930-1932.md]

THIS SUBJECT BELIEVES the question of whether machines think must be replaced by an operational test.
  @LAYER narrative  @AUTHOR ai  @CONFIDENCE 0.90
  @SOURCES [text/papers/computing-machinery-1950.md]
  @AS_OF 1950

THIS SUBJECT BELIEVES spirit and matter are connected but spirit may outlive the body weakly.
  @LAYER narrative  @AUTHOR ai  @CONFIDENCE 0.55
  @SOURCES [text/letters/morcom-1930-1932.md]
  @AS_OF 1932
  @NOTE Youthful conviction after Morcom's death; the mature position
  is materialist. Kept, dated, per the temporal-modeling rule — a
  belief held at nineteen is not overwritten by the man at forty.

THIS SUBJECT FRAMES fair play for machines as half a joke and wholly in earnest.
  @LAYER narrative  @AUTHOR ai  @CONFIDENCE 0.60
  @SOURCES [text/broadcasts/bbc-1951-1952.md,
            text/papers/computing-machinery-1950.md]

